review_blob: Smells like pickles and mint. Tastes of the same. I could see how it may be good in theory but it is way too overbearing in this beer. Shared with three others and nobody finished it.
beer_name: R & B Birra Fresca Cucumber Mint IPA

review_blob: 2012 December, 341ml bottle. Deep ruby red with little head and no retention. Light sweet aromas of toffee and dark fruits. Toffee, dark fruits, light tobacco with an earthy slight dry finish. Very smooth, malty and chewy with a very slight booziness. 11%! Where? Mmmm!

Light cloudy orange, pumpkin pie and bourbon aroma, vanilla, maple and pumpkin pie spices flavour. Finishes a bit thin with a maple vanilla sweetness and a wood astringency. Great aroma, decent taste but an odd finish.
beer_name: Phillips Crookeder Tooth Barrel Aged Pumpkin Ale

review_blob: Pours black with a rocky tan head with good lacing. Aromas of dark bitter chocolate, dark fruits and a little licorice. Taste is the same as the aroma with a nice slight bitter finish wich keeps it from being heavy on the palate. Rich and full of stout like flavours with a nice dry finish, all at 7.5%!

Dark brown with a reddish purple hue, big rocky tan head. Aromas of dark fruit, dark cocoa and a light musty funk. Tastes of juicy dark fruits, plum and cherry, dark chocolate and a light acidity. Full and rich mouth feel with a dry finish. Very enjoyable.

Brilliant golden colour with an egg white thin head. Aroma of light grains and a spicy/ herbal hop note. Firm spicy noble hop flavour with a light malt character and a soft but lingering hop bitterness. Great mouthfeel, creamy and soft. A very session able blonde ale.

Pours a reddish brown with a small light beige head, aromas of caramel malt, candi sugar and light alcohol. Tastes of malt sweetness light & caramel, good carbonataion and mouth feel. Overall a bit sweet(cloying) and lacks a Belgian character & complexity

Black with a small tan head, aroma of milk chocolate and coffee. Taste of dark chocolate & dark roasted coffee and a nice hop bitterness in the finish, silky, milky mouth feel that finishes dry, very nice stout!
Dark brown with a beige head. Aroma of coffee and nuts. Chocolate, coffee, light nutty caramel with a light lingering bitterness. Drink it!
beer_name: Howe Sound London Town English Brown

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: Batch 87 -Pours a deep dark reddish brown with a small beige head.  Aroma of chocolate, fig, dates and light smoke. Sweetness upfront followed by bitter chocolate and an earthy leathery finish. A light alcohol heat cleans up the palate leaves me wanting the next sip. Oh yeah!
